BEING CLOSE FRIENDS,

455
00:21:06,398 --> 00:21:08,433
BUT THIS IS
RIDICULOUS.

456
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:09,401
[Laughing]

457
00:21:09,968 --> 00:21:11,103
HEY, WHERE
YOU GOING?

458
00:21:11,136 --> 00:21:12,938
BACK TO THE LODGE.
I JUST FORGOT
SOMETHING.

459
00:21:12,971 --> 00:21:13,805
WHAT'S THAT?

460
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:14,873
I'M A COWARD.

461
00:21:14,906 --> 00:21:17,342
COME ON, CRAIG,
WE'RE ONLY
GONNA PRACTICE.

462
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:20,345
"PRACTICE." THE
LAST TIME I HEARD THAT
WAS FROM A FOOTBALL COACH

463
00:21:20,379 --> 00:21:22,981
AND 10 MINUTES LATER,
I HAD A BROKEN
COLLARBONE.

464
00:21:28,654 --> 00:21:30,656
[Yodeling]

465
00:21:35,594 --> 00:21:36,428
TODD?

466
00:21:37,429 --> 00:21:38,397
YEAH?

467
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:40,399
FORGET IT.

468
00:21:46,438 --> 00:21:48,407
A LITTLE LATE,
BOYS, AREN'T YOU?

469
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,642
YOU AND OLLIE
SHOW US HOW TO BRING

470
00:21:50,676 --> 00:21:52,678
AN INJURED SKIER
OFF THE MOUNTAIN.

471
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:00,085
VERY SLOPPY.

472
00:22:04,423 --> 00:22:07,092
SLOPPY.
VERY SLOPPY.

473
00:22:07,426 --> 00:22:10,562
NOW, LET'S SEE IF
YOU 2 BOYS CAN DO A
LITTLE BETTER THAN...

474
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:13,165
<i>ACHTUNG!</i>
<i>VOSS ICH LOSCH!</i>

475
00:22:13,198 --> 00:22:15,434
BOYS, BOYS, COME BACK.

476
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:16,868
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

477
00:22:17,202 --> 00:22:19,604
ACH, JUST LIKE
STALINGRAD.

478
00:22:19,638 --> 00:22:22,441
<i>ACHTUNG! </i>
 I SAY, HALT!

479
00:22:23,208 --> 00:22:25,444
COWARD, THIS IS
YOUR LAST CHANCE!

480
00:22:26,445 --> 00:22:29,715
I FEEL LIKE
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF
A WORLD WAR II MOVIE.

481
00:22:30,982 --> 00:22:32,417
[Grunting]

482
00:22:35,887 --> 00:22:37,622
[Girls laughing]

483
00:22:37,656 --> 00:22:38,623
WHAT'S THAT?

484
00:22:38,657 --> 00:22:40,192
SOUNDED LIKE
GIRLS LAUGHING.

485
00:22:40,225 --> 00:22:42,627
WE MUST BE NEAR
THE SWISS BORDER.

486
00:22:42,661 --> 00:22:45,630
NOW WE ARE GOING
TO LEARN HOW TO DO
THE SNOWPLOW.

487
00:22:45,664 --> 00:22:47,599
FIRST WE PICK UP
OUR POLES THIS WAY

488
00:22:47,632 --> 00:22:49,201
AND WE BEND
OUR KNEES

489
00:22:49,234 --> 00:22:51,470
AND POINT OUR
INNER EDGES IN,
THIS WAY.

490
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:53,805
BEND YOUR KNEES
AND BOB UP AND DOWN.

491
00:22:56,675 --> 00:22:58,610
[Girls laughing]

492
00:22:58,643 --> 00:22:59,644
AH.

493
00:23:00,645 --> 00:23:02,547
THIS MUST BE
THE PLACE.

494
00:23:02,581 --> 00:23:03,715
YEAH, SLOPE 6.

495
00:23:03,749 --> 00:23:04,883
[Todd]
OH, BOY.

496
00:23:04,916 --> 00:23:07,652
CRAIG, NOW THAT'S THE
WAY TO LEARN HOW TO SKI.

497
00:23:07,686 --> 00:23:09,654
NICE AND EASY
AND SLOW.

498
00:23:09,955 --> 00:23:12,591
YEAH. YEAH, IT'S TOO
BAD WE'RE NOT GIRLS.

499
00:23:12,624 --> 00:23:16,061
YOU KNOW, A FEW
LESSONS HERE, IN THE
BASIC FUNDAMENTALS

500
00:23:16,094 --> 00:23:18,497
AND WE'D BE
ABLE TO CLOBBER
FREDDIE, LIKE THAT!

501
00:23:18,530 --> 00:23:20,265
YOU REALLY THINK
WE COULD CATCH
ON THAT FAST?

502
00:23:20,298 --> 00:23:21,500
ARE YOU
KIDDING?

503
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:22,734
WE'RE
NATURAL ATHLETES.

504
00:23:22,768 --> 00:23:23,802
WE ARE?

505
00:23:23,835 --> 00:23:25,303
I'VE GOT A
GREAT IDEA.

506
00:23:25,337 --> 00:23:26,304
JUST A SECOND.

507
00:23:26,338 --> 00:23:27,672
WHAT'RE YOU
GONNA DO NOW?

508
00:23:27,706 --> 00:23:29,007
I'LL SPELL "HELP"
IN THE SNOW.

509
00:23:29,040 --> 00:23:30,509
THE LAST TIME YOU
HAD A GREAT IDEA

510
00:23:30,542 --> 00:23:33,478
<i>I GOT SUSPENDED</i>
<i>FOR 2 SEMESTERS.</i>

511
00:23:35,547 --> 00:23:37,115
[Laughing]

512
00:23:49,561 --> 00:23:51,763
LOOK AT THE
NEW COMPETITION.

513
00:23:51,797 --> 00:23:53,865
I CAN'T. I
JUST HAD LUNCH.

514
00:24:01,206 --> 00:24:02,607
ALL RIGHT,
NOW, LOOK.

515
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:04,342
IF WE DON'T
DISGUISE OUR VOICES,

516
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:05,977
WE'LL NEVER PULL
IT OFF, OLD GIRL.

517
00:24:06,011 --> 00:24:08,046
NOW, ONCE MORE,
FROM THE TOP.

518
00:24:08,079 --> 00:24:09,181
[Clearing throat]

519
00:24:09,214 --> 00:24:10,215
THE...

520
00:24:10,749 --> 00:24:12,517
[High voice]
"THE RAIN IN SPAIN

521
00:24:12,551 --> 00:24:14,352
"FALLS MAINLY
IN THE PLAINS."

522
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:16,555
RIGHT. NOW
THE OTHER.

523
00:24:16,588 --> 00:24:19,191
"HURRICANES
HARDLY EVER HAPPEN

524
00:24:19,224 --> 00:24:21,860
"IN HAMPTON,
HARTFORD OR HEREFORD."

525
00:24:21,893 --> 00:24:22,961
[High voice]
"SHE'S GOT IT.

526
00:24:22,994 --> 00:24:24,529
"BY GEORGE, I
THINK SHE'S GOT IT."

527
00:24:24,563 --> 00:24:25,797
THANK YOU.
NOTHING.

528
00:24:25,831 --> 00:24:27,332
TELL ME, JANE,
ONE QUESTION.

529
00:24:27,365 --> 00:24:28,633
WHAT'S THAT, DEAR?

530
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:30,802
[Normal voice]
DO BLONDES REALLY
HAVE MORE FUN?

531
00:24:30,836 --> 00:24:32,604
[Girls laughing]

532
00:24:35,774 --> 00:24:37,008
TALLYHO, THERE.

533
00:24:37,042 --> 00:24:38,510
TOODLE-OO.

534
00:24:38,543 --> 00:24:39,811
TALLYHO,
THERE.

535
00:24:39,845 --> 00:24:41,513
THE MAN HERE
AT THE LODGE SAID

536
00:24:41,546 --> 00:24:43,715
THE GIRL'S SKI
CLASS IS ON
SLOPE 6.

537
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:45,550
AND SINCE
WE'RE GIRLS--

538
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:46,751
AT LEAST WE WERE
THE LAST TIME
WE LOOKED.

539
00:24:46,785 --> 00:24:49,354
[Craig]
WE THOUGHT WE MIGHT
JUST TRY OUR HAND AT IT.

540
00:24:49,387 --> 00:24:51,756
WE'RE HERE ON A
HOLIDAY FROM SCHOOL.

541
00:24:51,790 --> 00:24:55,727
JUST LIKE YOU
CHAPS OR CHICKS,
UH, UH, LASSIES?

542
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:59,564
I DIDN'T KNOW THERE
WERE ANY ENGLISH
EXCHANGE STUDENTS HERE.

543
00:24:59,598 --> 00:25:03,001
OH, YES, YES,
WE EXCHANGED
EVERYTHING.

544
00:25:03,034 --> 00:25:04,703
A LONG
TIME AGO.

545
00:25:04,736 --> 00:25:06,371
[Whispers]
AT LEAST
10 MINUTES.

546
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:07,672
SHALL WE?

547
00:25:07,706 --> 00:25:08,607
TO THE SLOPES.

548
00:25:10,075 --> 00:25:11,576
[Todd]
BE CAREFUL.

549
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:12,544
[Craig]
WHAT FOR?

550
00:25:12,577 --> 00:25:13,578
IT FEELS GOOD.

551
00:25:13,612 --> 00:25:16,615
[Yodeling]

552
00:25:21,820 --> 00:25:23,788
THAT'S RIGHT,
VERY GOOD.

553
00:25:23,822 --> 00:25:25,790
JUST KEEP YOUR TOES
POINTED LIKE THIS.

554
00:25:25,824 --> 00:25:27,192
GOOD, IN
THE SNOWPLOW.

555
00:25:27,225 --> 00:25:28,760
GOOD, GOOD,
VERY NICE.

556
00:25:28,793 --> 00:25:31,563
[Girl]
NITA, COULD YOU COME
OVER HERE FOR A MINUTE?

557
00:25:31,596 --> 00:25:32,764
OH, STAY WHERE
YOU ARE, JANE.

558
00:25:32,797 --> 00:25:34,633
I'LL BE RIGHT
BACK, JUST STAY.

559
00:25:34,666 --> 00:25:37,402
HEY, HEY, DON'T LEAVE
ME LIKE THIS.

560
00:25:37,969 --> 00:25:40,605
WHERE'S THE BRAKES
ON THESE DARN THINGS?

561
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,441
[Yells]

562
00:25:43,675 --> 00:25:45,410
MY, YOUR FRIEND'S
A FAST LEARNER.

563
00:25:45,443 --> 00:25:47,145
LOOK HOW
NICELY SHE'S DOING.

564
00:25:47,178 --> 00:25:48,780
GOOD SHOW, TODD!

565
00:25:49,648 --> 00:25:50,882
TODD?

566
00:25:50,916 --> 00:25:53,418
TODD, UH,
JANE TODD.

567
00:25:53,451 --> 00:25:56,421
TODD, T-O-D-D,
ONE OF THE OLDEST
FAMILIES IN ENGLAND.

568
00:25:56,855 --> 00:25:58,690
WHOO!

569
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:03,628
STRETCHER BEARERS!

570
00:26:03,662 --> 00:26:06,631
STIFF UPPER LIP, JANE!
I'M COMING, OLD GIRL.

571
00:26:06,665 --> 00:26:08,733
BUT YOU CAN'T
SKI EITHER, NORA.

572
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:11,102
ARE YOU SERIOUS?
OF COURSE I...

573
00:26:11,136 --> 00:26:12,671
CAN'T.

574
00:26:12,704 --> 00:26:14,773
NITA! NITA!

575
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:18,677
YOU KEEP
PRACTICING, GIRLS,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

576
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:21,112
OH, YEAH,
YEAH.

577
00:26:21,146 --> 00:26:23,748
JANE GOT AWAY.
QUICK, DOWN THERE.

578
00:26:23,782 --> 00:26:24,783
WHY DID
SHE DO THAT?

579
00:26:24,816 --> 00:26:27,852
YOU TELL HER TO
GET BACK HERE
RIGHT NOW, LINDA.

580
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,689
I'VE GOT NO TIME
TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

581
00:26:30,722 --> 00:26:32,157
I'LL GET HER.

582
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:38,296
WAIT FOR ME,
DEARIE.

583
00:26:56,381 --> 00:26:58,216
NORA, YOU
CAN'T SKI.

584
00:26:58,249 --> 00:27:00,852
[Todd screams]

585
00:27:00,885 --> 00:27:02,721
WHOA!

586
00:27:02,754 --> 00:27:04,356
OH, CRAIG!

587
00:27:04,389 --> 00:27:05,757
HELP!

588
00:27:06,157 --> 00:27:07,726
WATCH OUT!

589
00:27:07,759 --> 00:27:08,693
[Craig screaming]

590
00:27:26,945 --> 00:27:28,980
AND I'LL NEVER CHEAT
IN EXAMS AGAIN.

591
00:27:29,014 --> 00:27:30,815
AND WHEN I GROW UP,

592
00:27:30,849 --> 00:27:33,685
I PROMISE NEVER TO
MAKE A LONG-DISTANCE
PHONE CALL

593
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:35,053
AND CHARGE IT TO
A WRONG NUMBER.

594
00:27:35,086 --> 00:27:36,287
WHOA!

595
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:37,689
WHOA!

596
00:27:42,594 --> 00:27:45,063
OF COURSE, KEEPING
ALL THESE PROMISES
WON'T BE EASY.

597
00:27:45,096 --> 00:27:47,932
BUT I'LL TRY STARTING
WITH THE EASY ONES FIRST.

598
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:50,168
LIKE, I PROMISE TO
BRUSH AFTER EVERY MEAL.

599
00:27:50,201 --> 00:27:51,970
YES, THAT'S A
GOOD START.

600
00:27:55,774 --> 00:27:57,742
MY LIPS ARE
GETTING CHAPPED.

601
00:27:58,877 --> 00:27:59,811
[Screaming]

602
00:28:34,345 --> 00:28:36,781
WHAT GOOD IS
A BOOK LIKE THIS
WITHOUT PICTURES?

603
00:28:44,255 --> 00:28:46,024
ALL RIGHT!
ALL RIGHT!

604
00:28:47,025 --> 00:28:49,327
WHAT'S YOUR
LICENSE NUMBER,
BUDDY?

605
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:50,829
HEY, HEY, HEY!

606
00:28:50,862 --> 00:28:52,931
WHAT'S YOUR
PHONE NUMBER,
HONEY?

607
00:28:52,964 --> 00:28:55,633
SAY, HOW WOULD
YOU LIKE A KICK
IN THE MOUTH?

608
00:28:55,667 --> 00:28:58,002
GREAT. PLAY HARD
TO GET, 'CAUSE
I JUST LOVE IT.

609
00:28:58,036 --> 00:28:59,003
YOU KNOW
SOMETHING?

610
00:28:59,037 --> 00:29:00,138
NO, WHAT'S THAT?

611
00:29:00,171 --> 00:29:01,806
THAT WAS
A MISTAKE.

612
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,074
[Laughing]

613
00:29:03,108 --> 00:29:04,809
HEY, THEY DON'T
MAKE GIRLS LIKE
YOU ANYMORE.

614
00:29:04,843 --> 00:29:06,578
OH, I HOPE NOT.

615
00:29:06,611 --> 00:29:07,846
HA.
HA.

616
00:29:11,516 --> 00:29:12,517
WHOA!

617
00:29:12,851 --> 00:29:14,486
[Screaming]

618
00:29:14,519 --> 00:29:15,854
[Crashing sound]

619
00:29:28,066 --> 00:29:29,033
[Laughing]

620
00:29:30,135 --> 00:29:31,903
OH, JANE.

621
00:29:32,871 --> 00:29:35,140
[Laughing]
MUST HAVE MADE
A WRONG TURN.

622
00:29:36,141 --> 00:29:37,642
I'LL BREAK IT.

623
00:29:37,675 --> 00:29:39,644
HA, HA, HA.
OH, YEAH.

624
00:29:39,677 --> 00:29:41,045
COME ON. I
DARE YOU TO.

625
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,648
NORA!

626
00:29:43,681 --> 00:29:44,849
FOR CRYING OUT
LOUD, LINDA,

627
00:29:44,883 --> 00:29:46,384
WILL YOU CLEAR
OUT OF HERE?

628
00:29:46,417 --> 00:29:48,887
CAN'T YOU SEE WE
WANT TO BE ALONE?

629
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:50,655
NORA!

630
00:29:50,688 --> 00:29:52,991
SORRY, BUT HE TRIED
TO GET FRESH WITH ME.

631
00:29:53,024 --> 00:29:54,893
I DON'T LIKE HIM
AT ALL, JANE.

632
00:29:54,926 --> 00:29:56,060
I DON'T
BLAME YOU.

633
00:29:56,094 --> 00:29:57,395
OH, NORA!

634
00:29:57,428 --> 00:29:59,898
HOW CAN YOU TALK
THAT WAY ABOUT
OUR FREDDIE?

635
00:29:59,931 --> 00:30:02,934
WHY, ALL THE
GIRLS IN SCHOOL
JUST LOVE HIM.

636
00:30:03,935 --> 00:30:06,437
SHE'S RIGHT,
YOU KNOW,
EVERY ONE OF THEM.

637
00:30:06,938 --> 00:30:09,307
COME ON, BABY.
I'LL WALK YOU
BACK TO THE LODGE.

638
00:30:09,340 --> 00:30:13,011
I SAY THERE,
BUT YOU REALLY DO
DIG PAIN, DON'T YOU?

639
00:30:13,344 --> 00:30:14,512
OH, NORA!

640
00:30:15,246 --> 00:30:17,348
NORA, COULD I
SPEAK TO YOU
FOR A MOMENT?

641
00:30:17,382 --> 00:30:18,650
PRIVATELY?

642
00:30:18,683 --> 00:30:20,118
OF COURSE,
MY DEAR.

643
00:30:22,053 --> 00:30:23,254
TOODLE-OO.

644
00:30:24,389 --> 00:30:26,658
OH, HEY, ARE ALL
YOU ENGLISH GIRLS
LIKE THAT?

645
00:30:26,691 --> 00:30:29,594
[Laughing]
OH, ONLY BEFORE
WE'RE MARRIED.

646
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:32,463
YEAH, WHAT HAPPENS
AFTERWARD?

647
00:30:32,931 --> 00:30:34,566
KARATE.
CHOP, CHOP!

648
00:30:34,599 --> 00:30:36,034
[Giggling]

649
00:30:36,701 --> 00:30:38,369
[Organ playing]

650
00:30:43,041 --> 00:30:45,677
LOOKS LIKE
I'VE GOT TO TEACH
YOU ABOUT MEN, NORA.

651
00:30:45,710 --> 00:30:47,579
MEN? HA! I KNOW
ALL ABOUT MEN.

652
00:30:47,612 --> 00:30:49,113
MY GOVERNESS
TOLD ME YEARS AGO.

653
00:30:49,147 --> 00:30:50,715
THE BIRDS
AND THE BEES.

654
00:30:50,748 --> 00:30:52,383
THE BEES JUMP
ON THE FLOWERS

655
00:30:52,417 --> 00:30:54,118
AND GET THEIR
FEET ALL STICKY,

656
00:30:54,152 --> 00:30:55,587
THEN THEY GO TO
ANOTHER FLOWER

657
00:30:55,620 --> 00:30:57,355
AND GET THEM
EVEN STICKIER.

658
00:30:57,388 --> 00:30:59,591
DOESN'T REALLY
SOUND LIKE
VERY MUCH FUN.

659
00:30:59,624 --> 00:31:01,759
ALTHOUGH,
I WOULD LIKE TO GET
MARRIED SOMEDAY

660
00:31:01,793 --> 00:31:04,629
IF THE RIGHT BEE,
UH, BOY SHOULD
COME ALONG.

661
00:31:04,963 --> 00:31:06,598
WELL, THEN, UH,

662
00:31:06,631 --> 00:31:09,934
I DON'T KNOW
HOW THINGS ARE
DONE IN ENGLAND,

663
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:12,136
BUT, WELL, WHAT
YOU JUST DID
TO FREDDIE

664
00:31:12,170 --> 00:31:14,606
IS--IS NOT THE
WAY TO GET AND
KEEP A MAN HERE.

665
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:17,075
OH, TELL ME MORE,
LINDA, PLEASE.

666
00:31:17,108 --> 00:31:19,477
ALL RIGHT, BUT RAISE
YOUR RIGHT HAND FIRST.

667
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:21,412
OH, THIS IS
SO EXCITING.

668
00:31:21,746 --> 00:31:23,414
NOW I WANT
YOU TO SWEAR,

669
00:31:24,182 --> 00:31:27,418
"I, NORA, DO SOLEMNLY
SWEAR NEVER TO REVEAL

670
00:31:27,452 --> 00:31:30,221
"TO ANY BOYFRIEND,
FIANCE, HUSBAND,

671
00:31:30,255 --> 00:31:32,123
"SON OR GRANDSON
OF MINE,

672
00:31:32,156 --> 00:31:35,293
"THE FOLLOWING
INFORMATION WHICH
I AM ABOUT TO HEAR.

673
00:31:35,326 --> 00:31:37,128
"SO HELP ME
LIZ TAYLOR."

674
00:31:37,161 --> 00:31:38,830
LIZ...

675
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:41,566
I SWEAR IT.

676
00:31:41,599 --> 00:31:43,167
ALL RIGHT,
FIRST...

677
00:31:43,201 --> 00:31:45,737
[Man]
<i>IN ORDER TO COMPLY</i>
<i>WITH THE GOVERNMENT'S</i>

678
00:31:45,770 --> 00:31:47,939
<i>REQUEST TO KEEP THE</i>
<i>POPULATION EXPLOSION</i>

679
00:31:47,972 --> 00:31:49,307
<i>GOING AT FULL BLAST,</i>

680
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:52,110
<i>THE SOUND WILL BE</i>
<i>TURNED OFF FOR</i>
<i>THE NEXT FEW MOMENTS.</i>

681
00:31:52,143 --> 00:31:53,745
DO YOU THINK IT
WOULD BE ALL RIGHT

682
00:31:53,778 --> 00:31:55,313
IF I CALLED JANE
OVER TO LISTEN?

683
00:31:55,346 --> 00:31:57,081
SHE'S A GIRL,
ISN'T SHE?

684
00:31:57,115 --> 00:32:00,018
MAN, IF SHE ISN'T,
MOMSIE IS GOING TO
BE AWFULLY UPSET.

685
00:32:00,051 --> 00:32:03,087
WE'VE BEEN
SHARING THE SAME
