01:06:01,257 --> 01:06:02,892
HE'S STILL
GOING UP.

1392
01:06:03,659 --> 01:06:05,995
SIR ISAAC NEWTON
JUST TURNED
OVER IN HIS GRAVE.

1393
01:06:07,396 --> 01:06:09,031
JUST A LITTLE MORE.

1394
01:06:09,065 --> 01:06:11,033
JUST A LITTLE MORE.

1395
01:06:12,234 --> 01:06:13,502
WHOA!

1396
01:06:17,039 --> 01:06:19,075
HE'S SO FAT. WHY'S
HE SO FAT, CRAIG?

1397
01:06:19,108 --> 01:06:20,076
WHAT?

1398
01:06:20,109 --> 01:06:23,045
OH, WELL, HE, UH,
HAD A BIG BREAKFAST.

1399
01:06:23,079 --> 01:06:26,248
TODD ALWAYS EATS
A BIG BREAKFAST
BEFORE JUMPING.

1400
01:06:27,216 --> 01:06:29,085
PULL THE
STRING, YOU NUT.

1401
01:06:29,852 --> 01:06:32,421
THE WIND'S CHANGING.
I'D BETTER PULL IT.

1402
01:06:34,690 --> 01:06:36,058
I CAN'T FIND IT.

1403
01:06:36,292 --> 01:06:39,195
OH! OH!

1404
01:06:40,930 --> 01:06:42,765
THE STRING!
THE STRING!

1405
01:06:44,934 --> 01:06:46,702
I CAN'T
FIND IT!

1406
01:06:47,870 --> 01:06:50,639
"PLAY SPIN THE
BOTTLE." I'M A
VERY SICK BOY.

1407
01:06:51,140 --> 01:06:52,375
 OH!

1408
01:06:53,709 --> 01:06:54,744
WHAT CAN
WE DO?

1409
01:06:54,777 --> 01:06:57,079
WELL, UH,
WHEN HE REACHES
THE COASTLINE,

1410
01:06:57,113 --> 01:06:59,081
OUR RADAR WILL
PROBABLY PICK HIM UP.

1411
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:02,885
THEN A COUPLE OF
JETS WILL TAKE OFF
AND SHOOT HIM DOWN.

1412
01:07:03,152 --> 01:07:04,653
SHOOT HIM DOWN?

1413
01:07:10,326 --> 01:07:12,094
[Gun fires]

1414
01:07:12,128 --> 01:07:13,529
[Gun fires]

1415
01:07:13,562 --> 01:07:15,097
[Crowd gasping]

1416
01:07:16,132 --> 01:07:17,166
[Gun fires]

1417
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:19,068
[Screaming]

1418
01:07:21,137 --> 01:07:23,672
WHOA!

1419
01:07:25,408 --> 01:07:27,176
[Todd screaming]

1420
01:07:29,678 --> 01:07:31,180
[Crashing sound]

1421
01:07:32,415 --> 01:07:34,083
[Girl]
YOU THINK HE'S ALL RIGHT?

1422
01:07:35,751 --> 01:07:37,153
[Craig]
YOU ALL RIGHT, TODD?

1423
01:07:37,186 --> 01:07:38,821
I THINK
IT'S BROKEN.

1424
01:07:39,422 --> 01:07:40,656
YEAH, IT'S
BROKEN.

1425
01:07:40,689 --> 01:07:41,924
NO, MY LEG.

1426
01:07:43,159 --> 01:07:44,393
OW!

1427
01:07:44,427 --> 01:07:45,127
IT'S BROKEN,
TOO.

1428
01:07:45,761 --> 01:07:46,896
[Todd]
OW!

1429
01:07:46,929 --> 01:07:48,397
[Clattering]

1430
01:07:48,431 --> 01:07:50,399
OW!

1431
01:07:50,433 --> 01:07:52,134
[Todd]
BUT, DOCTOR, I
GOT A DATE TONIGHT!

1432
01:07:52,168 --> 01:07:53,269
A BIG ONE.

1433
01:07:53,302 --> 01:07:55,137
CAN'T YOU JUST PUT
A BAND-AID ON IT?

1434
01:07:55,171 --> 01:07:57,173
I'LL COME BACK
TOMORROW FOR
THE SPLINT.

1435
01:07:57,206 --> 01:07:58,774
OH!

1436
01:08:02,945 --> 01:08:04,180
OH!

1437
01:08:04,713 --> 01:08:06,182
TODD, YOU'VE GOT
A BROKEN LEG.

1438
01:08:06,215 --> 01:08:08,150
YOU CAN'T GO
OUT TONIGHT.

1439
01:08:08,184 --> 01:08:09,585
OH, YES,
I CAN.

1440
01:08:09,618 --> 01:08:12,621
NITA LEFT ME A NOTE,
ALONG WITH A MAP TO
HER HOUSE. READ IT.

1441
01:08:12,655 --> 01:08:16,358
"HURRY. I AM
WAITING, DARLING."
SIGNED, "NITA."

1442
01:08:16,392 --> 01:08:18,828
"P.S. BRING THE
MILK BOTTLE."

1443
01:08:18,861 --> 01:08:20,930
TODD, YOU CAN'T GO
OUT WITH THAT LEG.

1444
01:08:20,963 --> 01:08:23,365
CRAIG, IF I
DON'T GO, THINK
WHAT IT'LL DO

1445
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:25,134
TO THE AMERICAN
IMAGE OVERSEAS.

1446
01:08:25,167 --> 01:08:26,202
BAD, HUH?

1447
01:08:26,235 --> 01:08:28,604
THE PEACE CORPS WILL
HAVE BEEN FOR NOTHING.

1448
01:08:28,637 --> 01:08:31,006
OH, AND, UH,
DON'T WAIT UP.

1449
01:08:31,040 --> 01:08:33,642
AND REMEMBER TO
CALL LINDA 10
MINUTES AFTER I LEAVE

1450
01:08:33,676 --> 01:08:35,211
AND TELL HER
WHERE I'M
HEADING. GOT IT?

1451
01:08:35,244 --> 01:08:36,378
GOT IT.
GOT IT.

1452
01:08:42,251 --> 01:08:43,252
GOOD LUCK.

1453
01:08:56,665 --> 01:09:00,202
DARNED IF I'LL
BE WITHOUT A DATE
OUR LAST NIGHT HERE.

1454
01:09:04,273 --> 01:09:06,842
ROOM, UH,
211, PLEASE.

1455
01:09:08,677 --> 01:09:11,180
HELLO, LINDA?
IS BARBARA THERE?

1456
01:09:11,213 --> 01:09:12,581
YEAH,
SHE'S HERE.

1457
01:09:13,449 --> 01:09:14,416
HOW'S TODD?

1458
01:09:14,450 --> 01:09:17,319
IN TERRIBLE
PAIN. TERRIBLE.

1459
01:09:17,353 --> 01:09:20,322
THEY GAVE HIM SOMETHING
AND HE WENT TO SLEEP
FOR ABOUT A HALF HOUR.

1460
01:09:20,356 --> 01:09:22,591
THEN HE WOKE UP, GOT
HIS MILK BOTTLE AND LEFT.

1461
01:09:23,092 --> 01:09:24,927
<i>COULD I SPEAK</i>
<i>TO "YOU KNOW"?</i>

1462
01:09:25,528 --> 01:09:27,229
"YOU KNOW,"
IT'S CRAIG.

1463
01:09:27,263 --> 01:09:28,864
TELL HIM TO GET LOST.

1464
01:09:29,298 --> 01:09:30,199
BARBARA.

1465
01:09:30,733 --> 01:09:32,501
ALL RIGHT, I'LL
TELL HIM MYSELF.

1466
01:09:32,535 --> 01:09:35,404
UH, CRAIG, SHE SAYS SHE
HAS A TERRIBLE HEADACHE.
SHE'LL CALL YOU LATER.

1467
01:09:35,437 --> 01:09:38,073
<i>GOODBYE.</i>
I'LL BET. THANKS A LOT!

1468
01:10:04,500 --> 01:10:06,335
ROOM 206, PLEASE.

1469
01:10:08,771 --> 01:10:11,307
HELLO, FREDDIE?
IS THAT YOU?

1470
01:10:24,453 --> 01:10:25,454
AH.

1471
01:10:25,487 --> 01:10:27,089
LET ME SEE.

1472
01:10:28,991 --> 01:10:31,527
"A LEFT TURN IN THE
FORK OF THE ROAD

1473
01:10:32,328 --> 01:10:34,296
"ACROSS THE FIELD."

1474
01:10:34,330 --> 01:10:35,564
AH!

1475
01:10:35,598 --> 01:10:37,800
ONLY ABOUT 2
MORE MILES TO GO.

1476
01:10:44,340 --> 01:10:47,109
IT CAN'T BE MUCH
FURTHER. IT CAN'T BE.

1477
01:10:50,546 --> 01:10:51,313
[Grunting]

1478
01:10:55,551 --> 01:10:57,353
HOW I LOVE
A CHALLENGE.

1479
01:11:04,026 --> 01:11:05,394
[Wolves howling]

1480
01:11:07,896 --> 01:11:09,398
[Grunting]

1481
01:11:25,648 --> 01:11:27,349
[Grunting]

1482
01:11:43,565 --> 01:11:46,368
[Growling]

1483
01:11:49,538 --> 01:11:50,606
GET OUT.

1484
01:11:56,512 --> 01:11:57,946
[Nita]
COME IN, DARLING.

1485
01:12:06,455 --> 01:12:07,456
WELL,

1486
01:12:07,890 --> 01:12:09,958
I CAME AS SOON
AS I COULD.

1487
01:12:14,596 --> 01:12:17,232
WELL. GET UP.

1488
01:12:17,266 --> 01:12:18,400
WHAT FOR?

1489
01:12:19,768 --> 01:12:21,570
THE TIME
HAS COME.

1490
01:12:30,479 --> 01:12:31,980
WHAT'S
THE MATTER?

1491
01:12:32,414 --> 01:12:33,482
NOTHING.

1492
01:12:34,416 --> 01:12:35,951
THEN COME HERE.

1493
01:12:35,984 --> 01:12:38,454
YOU PROMISED
TO PLAY SPIN
THE BOTTLE WITH ME.

1494
01:12:41,557 --> 01:12:43,225
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

1495
01:12:43,625 --> 01:12:45,260
TALK TO ME.

1496
01:12:46,061 --> 01:12:47,229
TALK?

1497
01:12:47,262 --> 01:12:49,998
YEAH, LIKE--LIKE
YOU DO TO THE
AMERICAN GIRLS.

1498
01:12:50,599 --> 01:12:53,502
I'VE BEEN WATCHING, AND
IT LOOKS PRETTY NICE.

1499
01:12:54,503 --> 01:12:55,604
NITA.

1500
01:12:55,637 --> 01:12:57,606
NITA, DON'T MAKE
FUN AT A TIME
LIKE THIS.

1501
01:12:57,639 --> 01:13:00,709
I'M NOT MAKING
FUN. I WANT YOU
TO TALK TO ME

1502
01:13:00,743 --> 01:13:03,445
AND TREAT ME LIKE YOU
DO THE AMERICAN GIRL.

1503
01:13:04,480 --> 01:13:05,481
THE AMERI...

1504
01:13:05,914 --> 01:13:07,916
NITA, I THOUGHT
THAT WE WERE
GONNA--

1505
01:13:07,950 --> 01:13:09,818
NO, FIRST
WE TALK

1506
01:13:10,319 --> 01:13:11,487
AND THEN CANDY...

1507
01:13:11,520 --> 01:13:13,422
AND THEN,
AFTER THAT, WE'LL.

1508
01:13:13,455 --> 01:13:15,257
THEN MORE TALK.

1509
01:13:15,290 --> 01:13:17,493
THEN, WE CAN
HOLD HANDS.

1510
01:13:18,293 --> 01:13:19,495
NO.

1511
01:13:19,528 --> 01:13:22,464
THEN YOU ASK FOR THE
KISS ON THE CHEEK.

1512
01:13:23,599 --> 01:13:26,101
AND THEN, MAYBE,
THE KISS ON THE CHEEK.

1513
01:13:26,769 --> 01:13:27,703
THEN...

1514
01:13:28,504 --> 01:13:30,339
THEN, WHAT
COMES NEXT?

1515
01:13:30,672 --> 01:13:32,241
I DON'T KNOW.

1516
01:13:32,274 --> 01:13:33,942
THAT'S AS FAR
AS I EVER GOT.

1517
01:13:45,854 --> 01:13:46,989
HI.

1518
01:13:50,626 --> 01:13:52,461
NOW, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING DRESSED LIKE THAT?

1519
01:13:52,494 --> 01:13:53,695
WE'RE PINNED.

1520
01:13:55,364 --> 01:13:56,532
OH,
CONGRATULATIONS.

1521
01:13:56,565 --> 01:13:58,767
I'M SURE YOU
AND BARBARA WILL
MAKE A VERY--

1522
01:13:58,801 --> 01:14:00,502
BARBARA?
WHAT BARBARA?
FREDDIE.

1523
01:14:01,570 --> 01:14:03,772
OH, COME
ON, KNOCK IT
OFF. VERY FUNNY.

1524
01:14:03,806 --> 01:14:06,675
I'M NOT BEING
FUNNY. HE GAVE ME
HIS FRATERNITY PIN.

1525
01:14:06,708 --> 01:14:08,777
BUT HE CAN'T
DO THAT.

1526
01:14:08,811 --> 01:14:11,113
HE'S A BOY AND--
AND SO ARE YOU.

1527
01:14:11,146 --> 01:14:12,581
WE'LL WORK
IT OUT.

1528
01:14:14,216 --> 01:14:16,652
YOU MEAN THAT.
I REALLY...

1529
01:14:17,553 --> 01:14:20,689
I'M GETTING YOU
OUT OF HERE,
TONIGHT. TAKE THIS.

1530
01:14:24,726 --> 01:14:26,562
[Knock at door]

1531
01:14:26,595 --> 01:14:27,896
WHO IS IT?

1532
01:14:28,330 --> 01:14:30,666
[Freddie]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN THERE, TODD?

1533
01:14:33,769 --> 01:14:35,003
[Pounding on door]

1534
01:14:35,037 --> 01:14:37,539
[Freddie]
I SAID, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING IN THERE?

1535
01:14:37,573 --> 01:14:39,541
NORA? NORA?

1536
01:14:39,575 --> 01:14:40,909
HE'S SO
JEALOUS.

1537
01:14:41,243 --> 01:14:43,812
[Pounding on door]

1538
01:14:43,846 --> 01:14:45,881
[Freddie]
NORA! NORA!

1539
01:14:45,914 --> 01:14:47,649
LET'S GO. OUT
THE WINDOW.

1540
01:14:47,683 --> 01:14:48,851
THAT FREDDIE'S
PRETTY HIP.

1541
01:14:48,884 --> 01:14:51,753
I'VE NEVER BEEN
TREATED SO NICELY
IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

1542
01:14:51,787 --> 01:14:53,555
I SAID, OUT!

1543
01:14:53,589 --> 01:14:56,325
[Freddie]
I'M GOING TO DO
SOMETHING TERRIBLE.

1544
01:14:56,358 --> 01:14:58,393
I MEAN REALLY
TERRIBLE!

1545
01:15:00,429 --> 01:15:02,331
[Freddie]
BETTER OPEN UP, TODD!

1546
01:15:02,364 --> 01:15:03,699
[Pounding on door]

1547
01:15:03,732 --> 01:15:04,600
 TODD!

1548
01:15:05,634 --> 01:15:07,336
YOU BETTER
OPEN UP!

1549
01:15:07,369 --> 01:15:09,838
[Craig]
FREDDIE THINKS I SHOULD
GET A NOSE JOB THIS SPRING.

1550
01:15:09,872 --> 01:15:12,274
[Todd]
I MAY GIVE YOU ONE,
TONIGHT. LET'S GO.

1551
01:15:13,809 --> 01:15:14,810
[Freddie]
NORA!

1552
01:15:15,811 --> 01:15:17,579
YOU KNOW,
HE COMES FROM A
VERY GOOD FAMILY.

1553
01:15:17,613 --> 01:15:19,348
HIS GREAT-GREAT--

1554
01:15:19,381 --> 01:15:20,616
SHH! IN
THAT WINDOW.

1555
01:15:55,617 --> 01:15:57,286
LET'S GO.
LET'S GO.

1556
01:15:57,319 --> 01:15:59,621
THE LEAST WE CAN DO
IS LEAVE HIM A NOTE.

1557
01:15:59,655 --> 01:16:01,123
I SAID,
LET'S GO.

1558
01:16:01,690 --> 01:16:03,625
IT JUST
ISN'T FAIR!

1559
01:16:09,698 --> 01:16:11,333
[Freddie]
NORA!

1560
01:16:15,771 --> 01:16:16,805
NO!

1561
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,675
NORA! NORA!

1562
01:16:21,143 --> 01:16:22,244
[Whistles]

1563
01:16:22,277 --> 01:16:23,478
TAXI!

1564
01:16:25,681 --> 01:16:26,815
[Man]
WHERE TO,
BUDDY?

1565
01:16:26,848 --> 01:16:28,850
JUST HEAD WEST.
I'LL TELL YOU
WHERE TO STOP.

1566
01:16:28,884 --> 01:16:30,786
IN. I SAID, IN!

1567
01:16:32,888 --> 01:16:34,656
[Craig]
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN
THEY ARREST US

1568
01:16:34,690 --> 01:16:35,857
FOR NOT PAYING
OUR BILL?

1569
01:16:35,891 --> 01:16:38,293
[Todd]
WE SHOULD ONLY
GET THAT LUCKY.

1570
01:16:45,901 --> 01:16:46,868
HELLO THERE.

1571
01:16:46,902 --> 01:16:48,770
HELLO.
FOLLOW THAT CAB.

1572
01:16:48,804 --> 01:16:49,805
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

1573
01:16:49,838 --> 01:16:50,839
JUST FOLLOW
THAT CAB!

1574
01:16:50,872 --> 01:16:52,207
I'M A VERY
SICK MAN.

1575
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:53,942
I DON'T WANT
TO HAVE TO
ASK YOU AGAIN.

1576
01:16:53,976 --> 01:16:55,510
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

1577
01:16:55,544 --> 01:16:58,880
BUT AT LEAST HELP ME
AIM IT IN THE
RIGHT DIRECTION.

1578
01:16:58,914 --> 01:17:02,684
THAT'S A GOOD BOY.
WATCH IT, CAREFUL.

1579
01:17:02,718 --> 01:17:04,786
WE'VE GOT TO
CATCH THEM,
YOU IDIOT.

1580
01:17:04,820 --> 01:17:06,688
ALL RIGHT.
LET ME START IT.

1581
01:17:07,856 --> 01:17:10,492
[Starts engine]

1582
01:17:11,860 --> 01:17:13,328
NORA!

1583
01:17:15,163 --> 01:17:16,898
BOB, WAKE UP
EVERYBODY,

1584
01:17:16,932 --> 01:17:17,966
AND DON'T FORGET
THE DRIVER!

1585
01:17:18,000 --> 01:17:19,134
WHAT FOR?

1586
01:17:19,167 --> 01:17:20,736
NEVER MIND,
GO ON!

1587
01:17:20,769 --> 01:17:22,904
JANET, WAKE UP ALL THE
GIRLS AND MAKE SURE
THEY'RE DRESSED.

1588
01:17:22,938 --> 01:17:24,373
MICKEY,
HAVE THE BUS
BROUGHT IN FRONT.

1589
01:17:24,406 --> 01:17:25,941
INDIAN, WE'LL GET
THE SKIS AND POLES.

1590
01:17:33,949 --> 01:17:35,083
NORA!

1591
01:17:38,854 --> 01:17:41,289
TODD, I WAS KIDDING.
YOU KNOW I WAS KIDDING.

1592
01:17:43,091 --> 01:17:45,327
YOU HAD ME SCARED
THERE FOR A MINUTE.

1593
01:17:45,360 --> 01:17:46,728
LET'S GO BACK.

1594
01:17:46,762 --> 01:17:48,563
I'M ALL RIGHT,
TODD. I SWEAR IT.

1595
01:17:48,597 --> 01:17:50,165
YOU WANT ME TO
TURN AROUND?

1596
01:17:50,198 --> 01:17:52,934
NO, WAIT. LET ME
SEE IF THAT ONE
LIGHT'S STILL FOLLOWING.

1597
01:17:52,968 --> 01:17:54,770
COME ON, TURN AROUND.
I WAS KIDDING.

1598
01:17:54,803 --> 01:17:57,506
YOU MAY BE KIDDING.
BUT THAT NUT
ON THAT BIKE ISN'T.

1599
01:17:57,539 --> 01:17:58,540
KEEP GOING.

1600
01:18:04,813 --> 01:18:06,782
SOME BOYFRIENDS
WE PICKED.

1601
01:18:06,815 --> 01:18:08,784
WHICH ONE?
YOURS OR MINE?

1602
01:18:09,384 --> 01:18:10,786
BOTH OF THEM.

1603
01:18:10,819 --> 01:18:12,754
ONE RUNS AWAY WITH
AN ENGLISH GIRL,

1604
01:18:12,788 --> 01:18:15,323
AND THE OTHER ONE
DISAPPEARS COMPLETELY.

1605
01:18:15,624 --> 01:18:17,125
WELL, WE DID
IT TO THEM.

1606
01:18:17,592 --> 01:18:19,261
WE DROVE
THEM TO IT.

1607
01:18:20,929 --> 01:18:23,765
EVERY TIME TODD
PUT HIS ARM AROUND ME
AND TRIED TO BE NICE

1608
01:18:23,799 --> 01:18:25,834
I LAUGHED
IN HIS FACE.

1609
01:18:26,802 --> 01:18:28,403
YOU MUST
BE KIDDING.

1610
01:18:28,937 --> 01:18:30,972
I CAN'T BELIEVE
MY EARS.

1611
01:18:31,006 --> 01:18:32,574
YOU CAN'T, HUH?

1612
01:18:33,809 --> 01:18:34,810
WHAT NEXT?

1613
01:18:35,477 --> 01:18:36,812
OH, JUST HANG
AROUND.

1614
01:18:37,345 --> 01:18:39,948
I DON'T FEEL LIKE
LAUGHING ANYMORE.

1615
01:19:12,881 --> 01:19:14,816
[Dog barking]

1616
01:19:19,121 --> 01:19:20,689
IS ANYBODY
HERE?

1617
01:19:21,056 --> 01:19:24,059
LOOK, THEY MUST
STILL BE SLEEPING.
IT'S ONLY 6:30.

1618
01:19:26,328 --> 01:19:28,697
WAKE UP!
WAKE UP!

1619
01:19:29,064 --> 01:19:30,132
WE NEED GAS.

1620
01:19:32,067 --> 01:19:33,835
WAKE UP,
I SAY!

1621
01:19:34,636 --> 01:19:35,637
OH!

1622
01:19:39,341 --> 01:19:41,042
WHO THE DEVIL
ARE YOU?

1623
01:19:41,076 --> 01:19:42,878
WE WANT SOME GAS.
WOULD YOU...

1624
01:19:43,879 --> 01:19:45,380
FILL HER UP,
